      <title>Player-versus-player strategies</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=12329#M12329</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Hello!&amp;nbsp; Can someone with experience in this matter start a kind of newbie primer on strategies for someone just starting out in PvP?&amp;nbsp; As I only play blue servers, I don't personally need to know the ins and outs of playing on a red server, but if anyone has tips on that go ahead and post them, as this thread may be useful to others.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What I'm most interested in here though are what spells and buffs are useless against other players, what skills are most important to hone, etc.&amp;nbsp; In short, what makes fighting a player different from fighting a mob?&amp;nbsp; Leave no stone unturned, and assume NO knowledge on my part whatsoever.&amp;nbsp; Keep in mind I have never had a character of ANY sort higher than level 17, and have only been playing since October.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
