    <item>
      <title>Re: Player-versus-player strategies</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=12459#M12459</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I am not very well versed on what spells work/don't work in PvP.&amp;nbsp; I know we had some threads on that on the old boards.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Magic Resist is one of your "stats".&amp;nbsp; If you look at your (standard non-custom UI view) Inventory screen, to the upper left you see you name, level, class, etc.&amp;nbsp; Then your HP, AC... further down, about half way are your fire, cold, poison, disease and magic resists.&amp;nbsp; The higher the number, the better.&amp;nbsp; Yes, every bit helps but to be over 100 is best.&amp;nbsp; Ice is particularly looking at raising her MR, her cold/fire are fine in her normal gear.&amp;nbsp; Her poison and disease are iffy.&amp;nbsp; Her magic is not going to save her.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;To raise your magic resist (so that those spells don't land on you) you need gear and augments.&amp;nbsp; When people say things about plus 5 to all saves, they are talking about those same resists.&amp;nbsp; Just like other stats some foods can help too, can't think of a magic one off hand but wouldn't be surprised if there is one.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;When you look at gear with stats, it will have the name of the item, the damage/delay if it is a weapon, and any stats or effects it has.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It all adds up, so each plus 1, plus 5, plus whatever you get helps.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
